INSTALLATION

This package contains two different, alternative implementations of one and 
the same plugin.

Simply copy either the ./ruby/* version or the ./vim7/* version of the plugin 
to your vim plugins folder. They need either ruby (but can work on vim6 as well 
if it has the ruby extension) or vim7 (which requires vim7 but does not depend 
on ruby).

NOTE: You only need _one_ of the plugins, not both.

=============================================================================
CONFIGURATION

By default the plugin only knows how to toggle between these three pairs:
    on <-> off;  yes <-> no;  true <-> false

but it can easily be extended with your own pairs of words to be toggled from 
your .vimrc, like this:

" Sample ToggleWords dictionary for +ruby version:
let g:toggle_words = 
   \ "on off yes no true false " .
   \ "online offline " .
   \ "in out left right top bottom up down " .
   \ "all none " .
   \ "allow deny accept reject " .
   \ "min max hi lo high low " .
   \ "first last prev next pred succ inc dec " .
   \ "odd even " .
   \ "hidden visible show hide " .
   \ "open close " .
   \ "+ - < > 1 0 " .
   \ "vim emacs"

" Sample ToggleWords dictionary for Vim7 version:
let g:toggle_words = {
   \ 'on' : 'off', 'yes' : 'no', 'true' : 'false',
   \ 'online' : 'offline',
   \ 'in' : 'out', 'left' : 'right', 'top' : 'bottom', 'up' : 'down',
   \ 'all' : 'none',
   \ 'allow' : 'deny', 'accept' : 'reject',
   \ 'min' : 'max', 'hi' : 'lo', 'high' : 'low',
   \ 'first' : 'last', 'prev' : 'next', 'pred' : 'succ', 'inc' : 'dec',
   \ 'odd' : 'even',
   \ 'hidden' : 'visible', 'show' : 'hide',
   \ 'open' : 'close',
   \ '+' : '-', '<' : '>', '1' : '0',
   \ 'vim' : 'emacs',
   \ }

Just copy the appropriate example to your .vimrc and adjust it as needed.

That's it.
